SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 364
By Pody
A RESOLUTION to recognize and commend the Tennessee
Small Band Association's second annual state
championship.
WHEREAS, for decades, Tennessee marching band state championships have been
divided into three levels: the Division I state championship, the Division II state championship,
and the Contest of Champions at Middle Tennessee State University; and
WHEREAS, the Tennessee Secondary School Athletic Association (TSSAA) allows five
classes in volleyball; six classes in basketball, baseball, and softball; and nine classes in
football; and
WHEREAS, there is a need for a marching band state championship for public schools
with very small marching bands; and
WHEREAS, several public schools convened in 2022 and created the Tennessee Small
Band Association (TSBA) and the TSBA Celebration marching championship to represent public
schools with an enrollment of 500 or less, according to TSSAA enrollment figures, with
marching bands of thirty or less winds and percussion; the physical awards for such
championships are known as the Senate Trophy; and
WHEREAS, the Watertown High School Band and band director Scott Corley hosted the
second annual Tennessee Small Band Association State Championship on November 2, 2024;
and
WHEREAS, we congratulate the fourth-place band, Trousdale County High School, and
director Robert A. Joines, II; third-place band, Perry County High School, and director Marlana
Nyholt; TSBA state champion soloist Rhoslyn Hunter and second-place band, Gordonsville High
