School, and director Tiffanii Brown; and TSBA state champion and winner of the Senate Trophy,
Hollow Rock-Bruceton High School Band, and director Keith Breeden; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we honor those estimable teachers who have dedicated their
time and energies to educating their students and providing scholarship and competitive
opportunities for students in secondary schools throughout the State; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we recognize and commend the winners of the
Tennessee Small Band Association's second annual state championship and extend to all those
involved in organizing and producing this tremendous event our best wishes for much continued
success in their future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
